cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the formal verification of program behavior, specifically the I/O behavior, using Petri nets and separation logic. This falls under the category of formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of prophecy variables, which are a type of program variable used in formal verification, placing it under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also deals with equivalence reasoning, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
